description.p:
As described above, viewability or access to a user's pages can be limited to



    

Family only—only friends labeled as Family can see the page;

BFFs—only friends labeled as Family and BFF can see the page;

Trading/Gaming buddies—only friends labeled as Family, BFF and Trading/Gaming buddies can see the page;

All friends—all friends on the friends list can see the page;

Everyone—everyone in the entire virtual world can see the page;

Just Me—no one, other than the owner of the page, can see the page.

claim.claim-text:
1. A method, comprising the steps of:
on a computer, producing a user interface operable by a user, which allows selection of a first template from a plurality of templates, each one of said templates for arrangement of a personalizable portion of a website, where said templates define characteristics of a layout of said website and also define which rooms associated with said user will be displayed, and which other user rooms, associated with other users of the site other than the user, will be displayed;
receiving entry of a code from the user on the website;
verifying the code on the website;
responsive to said verifying the code, allowing the user to use an additional template other than said plurality of templates as said first template, for said arrangement of said personalizable portion of the website, where said additional template is not usable for said arrangement of said personalizable portion of the website prior to entry of the code and where said additional template defines all of: said rooms associated with said user which will be shown to others, different images which can be used on the website to be shown to others, and dynamic content on the website which changes periodically; and
automatically using said first template to arrange an arrangement of the user's website.

9. A method, comprising the steps of:
allowing selection of a first template from a plurality of templates, said templates for arrangement of a personalizable portion of a website, where each said template defines characteristics of a layout of said website and also defines which of a plurality of other user rooms will be displayed;
allowing selection of a time associated with said first template; and
automatically using said first template to define the characteristics of the website only for a first limited time that is based on said time, and after said first limited time, arranging said personalizable portion of a website based on a different template, other than said first template, and allowing for a setting of a new limited time after expiration of said first limited time;
receiving entry of a code from a user on the website;
verifying the code on the website; and responsive to said verifying the code, allowing the user to use an additional template for said arrangement of said personalizable portion of the website, where said additional template is not usable for said arrangement of said personalizable portion of the website prior to the user entering the code; and
wherein said template sets a characteristic of dynamic content that will be displayed including setting how often dynamic content will be changed.

16. A method, comprising the steps of:
allowing selection of a template from a plurality of templates, said templates for arrangement of a personalizable portion of a website, where each said template defines characteristics of a layout of said website, defines which of a plurality of other user rooms will be displayed, defines display of dynamic content which changes at specified intervals, and also defines said intervals;
allowing participation in activities on said website;
assigning scores for said participation in said activities, said scores based on said participation in said activities;
determining if a user has reached a certain score in a first activity on the website; and
responsive to said determining that said user has reached said certain score in said first activity, allowing the user to use an additional template for arrangement of said personalizable portion of a website, where said additional template is not usable for said arrangement of said personalizable portion of the website prior to the user reaching said certain score, and where said additional template defines different dynamic content than content in said plurality of templates and defines a different rotation interval that sets how often said dynamic content is updated.
